<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>This class calls <db:link xlink:href="qproperty.xml#beginPropertyUpdateGroup">Qt::beginPropertyUpdateGroup</db:link>() in its constructor and <db:link xlink:href="qproperty.xml#endPropertyUpdateGroup">Qt::endPropertyUpdateGroup</db:link>() in its destructor, making sure the latter function is reliably called even in the presence of early returns or thrown exceptions.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para><db:link xlink:href="qproperty.xml#endPropertyUpdateGroup">Qt::endPropertyUpdateGroup</db:link>() may re-throw exceptions thrown by binding evaluations. This means your application may crash (std::terminate() called) if another exception is causing <db:link xlink:href="qscopedpropertyupdategroup.xml">QScopedPropertyUpdateGroup</db:link>'s destructor to be called during stack unwinding. If you expect exceptions from binding evaluations, use manual <db:link xlink:href="qproperty.xml#endPropertyUpdateGroup">Qt::endPropertyUpdateGroup</db:link>() calls and try/catch blocks.</db:para>
</db:note>
